-- в”Ђв”Ђ Crafty Controller в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Crafty Controller is a free, open-source web control panel for launching, managing, and monitoring Minecraft Java and Bedrock server instances.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Free (open source, donation-supported)$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(NULL, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Crafty Controller Review: Free Minecraft Server Panel$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Crafty Controller is a free, self-hosted web panel for running and managing Minecraft Java and Bedrock server instances from any browser or device.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Crafty Controller is a free and open-source web-based control panel for launching, managing, and monitoring Minecraft server instances, distributed under the GNU General Public License v3. It is built with Python (3.10 or newer) and the Tornado web server, and its source code is publicly maintained on GitLab under the Crafty Controller project (with an earlier version's history on GitHub). The tool runs on Windows, Linux, and macOS, and offers pre-built Docker images and UnRAID templates for containerized or NAS-based deployments, along with a progressive web app for monitoring servers from a mobile browser. Crafty Controller supports any Minecraft server distribution that runs from a Java executable file вЂ” including vanilla, Paper, Spigot, Waterfall, CatServer, and modpack-based servers such as All The Mods вЂ” as well as Bedrock Edition server executables, making it useful for both Java and Bedrock server communities. Through its web interface, administrators can create and run multiple server instances, start and stop them independently, manage player lists and permissions, execute server console commands remotely, edit server configuration files and world files through a built-in file manager, and schedule recurring automated tasks such as backups and restarts. Security features include Argon2 password hashing for stored credentials, SSL/TLS certificate support for encrypting the web interface, and a fully self-hosted architecture, meaning all server data, configuration, and backups remain on the operator's own hardware rather than passing through a third-party cloud service. Because Crafty Controller is open source and self-hosted, there is no company behind it in the traditional SaaS sense, no pricing tiers, and no subscription plans вЂ” it is entirely free to download, install, and modify. The project is sustained by voluntary community donations through platforms like Ko-fi and Patreon rather than commercial licensing revenue. This makes Crafty Controller most comparable to other self-hosted game server management panels such as Pterodactyl or Multicraft, rather than to hosted Minecraft server providers. It is best suited for hobbyists, small communities, and system administrators who already have (or want) a server or VPS to host Minecraft on and prefer a web-based management layer over manually SSHing in and running server jar files by hand. Because it requires the user to provide and maintain their own server hardware or hosting, Crafty Controller is not a turnkey hosting service вЂ” it is purely the management and orchestration layer that sits on top of self-provided infrastructure. Its Docker and UnRAID support in particular have made it popular among home-lab and self-hosting communities that already run other containerized services.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '27d05620-43c3-4522-a6b6-5ae2a23a50b9';

